WEBVTT

NOTE
Pine Tree Fire Simulation — AF31 Treated vs Untreated Christmas Tree
Duration: ~1 minute 38 seconds
Recorded: December 2021

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
[Two pine trees shown side by side outdoors — fire truck visible in background]

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:18.000
[On-screen text: left tree "AF31 Treated", right tree "Untreated"]

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:30.000
[Firefighter approaches with 1300°C blowtorch — applies flame to the untreated tree on the right]

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Untreated tree ignites immediately — engulfed in high flames within seconds, fully consumed in under one minute]

00:00:50.000 --> 00:01:05.000
[Firefighter applies same blowtorch to the AF31 treated tree on the left — no ignition, fire does not spread]

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:15.000
[On-screen text: "Zero Ignition" — treated tree shows no fire propagation]

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:25.000
[On-screen text: "Eco-Friendly · Water Based · Unlimited Utility"]

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:38.000
[AF31 solution applied to extinguish remaining flames on the untreated tree — fire fully suppressed, no re-ignition]
